==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Circumdenudation
<hw>Cir`cum*den`u*da"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>circum-</ets> + <ets>denudation</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<def>Denudation around or in the neighborhood of an object.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hills of circumdenudation</b></col>, <cd>hills which have
been produced by surface erosion; the elevations which have been left,
after denudation of a mass of high ground.</cd>
<rj><au>Jukes.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Circumduce</ent>⟦br⟧
